PHP Timeclock - Account Password Recovery


THE SITUATION:

There is no "forgot password" flow anywhere in PHP Timeclock -- chngpasswd.php requires
already being logged in, and setup.php refuses to run again once config.inc.php exists (it
only ever creates the single initial admin account). If the admin password is lost, or any
other user's password is lost and no other admin account is available to reset it, the only
way back in is a direct database update.


RESETTING A PASSWORD:

--- Generate a bcrypt hash for the new password (do this on any machine with PHP, it doesn't
    need to be the server):
        php -r 'echo password_hash("choose-a-strong-password", PASSWORD_DEFAULT);'
--- Connect to the PHP Timeclock database with the mysql client, using the credentials from
    config.inc.php ($db_hostname, $db_username, $db_password, $db_name).
--- Run, replacing <hash> with the value the command above printed and <username> with the
    exact empfullname of the account to reset:
        UPDATE employees SET employee_passwd = '<hash>' WHERE empfullname = '<username>';
    A bcrypt hash never contains a single quote, so it's always safe to paste directly between
    the quotes in that statement.
--- Log in with the username and the password you chose (not the hash).

This works for any employees row, not just the admin account -- the same steps apply if a
Time Admin, reports, or ordinary punchclock user's password needs to be reset and no admin is
available to do it through chngpasswd.php.
